    "recap_headline": "Georgia Southern University",
    "recap_text": "Harrisonburg, Va. \u2014\nThe Georgia Southern baseball team (5-14, 0-3 SBC) dropped the series finale to James Madison (10-8, 3-0 SBC) by a 12-6 score on Sunday afternoon (March 15th) at Veterans Memorial Stadium.\nHOW IT HAPPENED:\nMason Gazaway\nled off the game by being plunked by a pitch before advancing to second by\nJames McCoy\n. A batter later,\nJack Myers\nroped a line drive perfectly in the left-center gap to score Gazaway and take the early 1-0 lead.\nThe Eagles doubled their lead off a solo home run from\nBennett Edwards\nto right-center field.\nIn the Dukes' second, they would get the runs back and more off of seven hits on their way to take a 6-2 lead.\nSouthern kept their bats hot the following frame, scoring two off RBI-singles from both\nSean White\nand\nNico Senese\nto cut the deficit to just two.\nAlex Mason\nwould come in for DeGondea to start the third and would start his appearance off with two scoreless frames, including two Ks in the Dukes' fourth.\nJames Madison added another run in the fifth as a hit batter, stolen base and beating a fielder's choice throw to third saw Jack Canizzaro drive home Thompson off a sac-fly.\nIn the Dukes' sixth, a Langley RBI-single pushed their lead to 8-4 before a sac-fly from Moody added a ninth run across.\nThe Dukes made it three straight innings of scratching a run across as a leadoff double from Thompson found him aboard third after a sac-bunt. A pass ball to score him increased their advantage to six.\nThe Eagles managed to scratch two across in the ninth to avoid a sixth straight scoreless inning by a Gazaway single and an RBI double from McCoy, as well as White's second RBI on the afternoon on a groundout.\nNOTES:\nBennett Edwards\nknocked his first career homer in the second inning on the afternoon, now giving eight different Eagles a homer on the year.\nA now double-digit hit streak was kept alive today as Myers upped his to ten games.\nJames McCoy\nhas now doubled in four of his last seven games, including two on the afternoon.\nAlex Mason\nprovided good relief work on the day, giving up no hits, but just one run, in his full three innings of work. He sat three Dukes down on strikes, including two of them in the fourth inning.\nUP NEXT:\nThe Eagles conclude their five-game road stretch with a midweek bout at Kennesaw State on Tuesday (March 17th). First pitch is set for 6 PM against the Owls."
  },
